{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772465199,"nonce":"B5pyTQtSZYO2BegwBx8jBO52DLk=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87vH_OW","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/327","origin":"github"},"title":"Enforce ROS 2 launch file naming convention (*_launch.py)","message":"## Context\n\nROS 2 officially recommends naming Python launch files with the `*_launch.py` suffix\n(e.g., `turtlesim_mimic_launch.py`), as documented in the\n[ROS 2 launch tutorials](https://docs.ros.org/en/rolling/Tutorials/Intermediate/Launch/Launch-system.html).\n\nBoth `*.launch.py` and `*_launch.py` are recognized by `ros2 launch`, but `*_launch.py`\nis the consistent pattern across official tutorials and is encouraged for discoverability\nand tool compatibility.\n\nProject repos in this workspace currently use a mix of conventions. For example,\n`ben_gazebo` uses `*.launch.py` naming, which diverges from the recommendation.\n\n## Task\n\nInvestigate and decide how to enforce the `*_launch.py` naming convention across\nproject repos:\n\n1. **Audit**: Identify which project repos already follow `*_launch.py` vs. which use `*.launch.py` or other patterns.\n2. **Decision**: Decide whether to enforce this as a workspace standard (and record in an ADR or coding convention doc).\n3. **Enforcement**: If adopted, add a pre-commit hook or CI check that flags Python launch files not following `*_launch.py`.\n4. **Migration**: Determine whether existing non-conforming launch files should be renamed, and whether that should happen as part of this issue or be tracked per-repo.\n\n## References\n\n- [ROS 2 docs — Integrating launch files into packages](https://docs.ros.org/en/rolling/Tutorials/Intermediate/Launch/Launch-system.html)\n- Related: `ben_description#9` (new launch files will be created; should follow the adopted convention)\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `GitHub Copilot CLI Agent`\n**Model**: `claude-sonnet-4.6`","files":null}]}